acSS7MTP2M3bSlDiscardCongThreshold.name: acSS7MTP2M3bSlDiscardCongThreshold
acSS7MTP2M3bSlDiscardCongThreshold.description: This parameter concerns feature that prevents uncontrolled increase of the MTP2 Transmit queue when the upper levels ignores the usual flow control mechanism. Any new SL_TX_MSU_RQ is discarded when the number of msu queued on the TB or RTB overtakes the threshold. Value 0, means that this feature is not activated. Access: Offline. AC INI-Param: SS7M3bSlDiscardCongThreshold
